The paper focuses on the task of visual question answering (VQA), which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes several mechanisms for incorporating attention and structured learning, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates its models on two popular datasets, which involves information retrieval and information extraction (cs.IR).
